t_comment_created": 1784110596368, "content": "", "score_down": 0, "author_flair_text": "", "pro_tier": 0, "is_stickied": false, "is_nsfw": false, "is_deleted": false, "is_image": true, "comments": 7, "score_up": 295, "is_edited": false, "is_moderator": false, "awards": 0, "vote_state": 2, "link_metadata": {"status": 200}, "post_flair_text": "", "archive_id": ""}, {"is_locked": false, "tweet_id": "", "sticky_comment": 0, "is_video_mp4": false, "type": "text", "uuid": "1ATBqjldES", "is_twitter": false, "is_admin": false, "score": 24, "suggested_sort": 0, "post_flair_class": "", "id": 8729594, "raw_content": "From today's EPOCH TIMES...\r\n\r\nTRINIDAD, Texas (pop. 800) \u2014The police chief has resigned, a municipal judge has been ousted, city workers have been fired, and lawsuits are piling up - after **police arrested a local woman on felony charges over a Facebook post** questioning the safety of the town\u2019s tap water.\r\n\r\n\u2018A Tornado of Craziness\u2019\r\n\r\nJailed for 23 hours without bond.  \r\n\r\nTrinidad Police Chief Charles Gregory doubled down on his assertion that Combs **broke the law by \u201cspreading false information\u201d on Facebook.**\r\n\r\n(only on the Right, of course - NEVER on the LEFT) \r\n\r\n\u201cWe have plenty of evidence that this was all a concerted effort to silence my client for uncovering and talking about the water problems there that they were trying to cover up.\u201d\r\n\r\nCombs did not fabricate an emergency or summon emergency responders or trigger evacuations, the lawsuit states. It further alleges that Combs\u2019s arrest was an act of \u201cdeliberate political retaliation.\u201d\r\n\r\nmore -  /Subscription needed/ \r\n\r\nhttps://www.theepochtimes.com/", "author": "Bullet3250", "created": 1784118378209, "profile_picture": "", "community": "TheDonald", "ad_tier": 2, "last_comment_author": "RU_joe_king", "is_video": false, "video_link": "", "is_new_user": false, "domain": "", "is_crosspost": false, "preview": "", "removal_source": "", "link": "", "author_flair_class": "", "is_removed": false, "media": {"resized_resolutions": [], "blurhash": "", "full_resolution": []}, "title": "A small Texas town has been turned upside down after a woman was arrested over her comments on the town\u2019s water quality...\r\n\r\n", "last_comment_created": 1784121675971, "content": "<p>From today's EPOCH TIMES...</p>\n<p>TRINIDAD, Texas (pop. 800) \u2014The police chief has resigned, a municipal judge has been ousted, city workers have been fired, and lawsuits are piling up - after <strong>police arrested a local woman on felony charges over a Facebook post</strong> questioning the safety of the town\u2019s tap water.</p>\n<p>\u2018A Tornado of Craziness\u2019</p>\n<p>Jailed for 23 hours without bond.</p>\n<p>Trinidad Police Chief Charles Gregory doubled down on his assertion that Combs <strong>broke the law by \u201cspreading false information\u201d on Facebook.</strong></p>\n<p>(only on the Right, of course - NEVER on the LEFT)</p>\n<p>\u201cWe have plenty of evidence that this was all a concerted effort to silence my client for uncovering and talking about the water problems there that they were trying to cover up.\u201d</p>\n<p>Combs did not fabricate an emergency or summon emergency responders or trigger evacuations, the lawsuit states. It further alleges that Combs\u2019s arrest was an act of \u201cdeliberate political retaliation.\u201d</p>\n<p>more -  /Subscription needed/</p>\n<p><a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://www.theepochtimes.com/\" target=\"_blank\">https://www.theepochtimes.com/</a></p>\n", "score_down": 0, "author_flair_text": "", "pro_tier": 0, "is_stickied": false, "is_nsfw": false, "is_deleted": false, "is_image": false, "comments": 2, "score_up": 24, "is_edited": false, "is_moderator": false, "awards": 0, "vote_state": 2, "link_metadata": {"status": 200}, "post_flair_text": "", "archive_id": ""}, {"is_locked": false, "tweet_id": "", "sticky_comment": 0, "is_video_mp4":